@title "Adding more and more syntactic possibilities counteracts ease of use for editors, thus antagonizing the main advantage of wikis - their unbeatable simplicity. In addition to that, existing (possibly already structured) content in Wikipedia may have to be manually converted or even duplicated. Finally, the approach requires fairly deep changes and additions to the MediaWiki software with unknown effects on its scalability."
